It also involves algorithmic mechanism design, which is a subfield of computer science that focuses on designing algorithms for economic systems. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it involves the design of algorithms that can reason about agents' behavior. The sub-category of Electronic Commerce (cs.EC) is also relevant as it deals with the design of mechanisms for economic transactions. The paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it involves the design of algorithms for implementing allocation rules. Finally, the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) may also be relevant as the paper deals with the issue of incentive compatibility, which is a key concern in secure and trustworthy systems.
